{
  "text": "Chrysin, alone or in combination with other compounds, decreased Akt phosphorylation and potentially caused mitochondrial dysfunction in THP-1 and HL-60 leukemia cells. Esophageal squamous carcinoma [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Chrysin (IC 50 = 63 \uf06dM) induced cytotoxicity in KYSE-510 cells in dose-and time-dependent manners.",
